WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.005
-[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12.882 --> 00:16.886
♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:17.017 --> 00:20.585
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:20.716 --> 00:24.633
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.763 --> 00:28.028
♪ WHEN THE EDGE
OF SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

00:28.158 --> 00:30.769
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

00:30.900 --> 00:34.947
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT

00:36.993 --> 00:38.864
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

00:38.995 --> 00:42.346
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.349 --> 00:49.397
-♪ I'LL BE READY
-♪ I'LL BE READY

00:49.527 --> 00:51.486
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

00:51.616 --> 00:53.401
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

00:53.531 --> 00:56.665
♪ I'LL BE READY

00:56.795 --> 00:59.885
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:00.016 --> 01:03.019
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:20.776 --> 01:22.691
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:22.821 --> 01:26.086
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:27.826 --> 01:31.917
♪ NO! I'LL BE READY

01:32.048 --> 01:35.269
♪ I'LL BE READY,
NEVER YOU FEAR ♪

01:35.399 --> 01:37.227
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:37.358 --> 01:40.752
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.883 --> 01:43.929
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.060 --> 01:47.019
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:09.999 --> 02:13.263
-[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING
ON HEADPHONES]

02:29.366 --> 02:31.847
-GIVE ME MORE PLATES DOWN.

02:32.717 --> 02:34.502
-GO AHEAD, TRIM IT OUT NOW.

02:35.242 --> 02:37.722
-WE'VE PICKED UP 200 RPM.

02:37.853 --> 02:40.986
-ANNOUNCER:
JAMES LEWISTON DRIVING
HIS TRIPLE ENGINE "POWER PLAY"

02:41.117 --> 02:43.250
HAS THE SLIGHT EDGE OVER
MITCH BUCHANNON,

02:43.380 --> 02:46.818
WHO DRIVES FOR OWNER BEN EDWARDS
IN THE LIGHTNING-WHITE
36-FOOT "SCARAB."

03:02.617 --> 03:04.575
-STAY TO THE INSIDE LINE.
-I'M ON IT.

03:14.324 --> 03:16.457
-HE'S BACK IN FRONT
WITH HALF A LAP REMAINING.

03:22.027 --> 03:24.639
-SURF SKIER DEAD AHEAD.
-THAT'S C.J. SKIING.

03:24.769 --> 03:25.640
WHAT'S SHE DOING OUT HERE?

03:26.902 --> 03:28.208
LEWISTON'S GOING TO
RUN HER DOWN!

03:31.602 --> 03:32.951
-[SCREAMS]

03:33.082 --> 03:35.302
-MITCH.
-I'M PULLING BACK.

03:38.783 --> 03:41.003
-C.J.? C.J.!

03:44.093 --> 03:46.269
YOU OKAY?
-I'M FINE.

03:46.400 --> 03:48.140
-MITCH, WE'RE IN A RACE.

03:48.271 --> 03:51.013
-MAKE IT BACK TO SHORE?
-I'M FINE, JUST GO WIN.

04:01.153 --> 04:03.199
-MITCH, WE'LL NEVER CLOSE
IN TIME.

04:03.330 --> 04:04.505
-HANG ON, I'M GIVING
HER ALL SHE'S GOT.

04:05.157 --> 04:06.985
-COME ON, DAD!

04:07.116 --> 04:09.684
-BUCHANNON IS CLOSING THE GAP,
BUT HE'S RUNNING OUT OF WATER.

04:09.814 --> 04:12.164
-TRIM IT UP, MITCH!
TRIM IT UP!

04:12.295 --> 04:13.340
-COME ON, DAD!

04:18.127 --> 04:20.911
-LEWISTON CROSSES
THE FINISH LINE FIRST.

04:21.043 --> 04:23.828
HE'S THREE SECONDS UNDER LAST
YEAR'S WINNING TIME,
QUALIFYING...

04:27.310 --> 04:30.313
-GREAT RACE, MR. LEWISTON.
-DROP ME AT MY YACHT.

04:44.719 --> 04:46.111
-CONGRATULATIONS.

04:46.721 --> 04:48.462
-FORGET IT, MAN. NOTHING YOU SAY
IS GOING TO MATTER.

04:48.592 --> 04:50.638
-WELL, HE'S GONNA
HEAR IT ANYWAY.

04:52.379 --> 04:54.206
IS WINNING A RACE
WORTH KILLING SOMEONE?

04:55.295 --> 04:58.080
-SHE'S ALIVE,
SO YOUR QUESTION IS MOOT.

04:58.210 --> 05:00.343
-MOOT? WHAT MOOT?
-NICE WORD.

05:00.474 --> 05:02.127
-YOUR WIN IS MOOT!

05:02.258 --> 05:04.478
WE STOPPED TO HELP SOMEBODY
YOU ALMOST KILLED.

05:05.348 --> 05:09.439
-IT'S NOT MY FAULT YOU'RE
A MORE DEDICATED LIFEGUARD
THAN A RACE BOAT DRIVER.

05:13.704 --> 05:15.358
-I'M GOING TO GO TALK
TO HIM, OKAY?

05:15.489 --> 05:18.448
-MITCH, IT'S NOT
GONNA DO ANY GOOD.

05:19.188 --> 05:22.322
-AH, JAMES, SPLENDID RACE.

05:22.452 --> 05:24.976
YOUR TIME SHOULD QUALIFY YOU
FOR FIRST IN THE FINALS
AGAIN THIS YEAR.

05:25.107 --> 05:27.239
-THANK YOU, YOUR HIGHNESS.

05:27.370 --> 05:30.417
TO WINNING THE RANDENBERG CUP ON
BEHALF OF THE RANDENBERG FAMILY.
-[GLASSES CLINK]

05:30.547 --> 05:33.376
-AS WELL AS THE HAND
OF THE PRINCESS WHO
PRESENTS IT TO YOU.

05:33.507 --> 05:34.986
-WHERE IS CATHERINE?

05:55.616 --> 05:58.836
-JAMES, TAKE ME
TO THE BEACH NOW. PLEASE?

05:59.402 --> 06:02.318
-YOUR FATHER'S THROWING
A PARTY, CATHERINE.
PROTOCOL DOESN'T--

06:02.449 --> 06:05.060
-I HATE PROTOCOL.
I'M SICK OF PARTIES.

06:05.669 --> 06:09.630
I JUST WANT TO LAY ON THE BEACH
IN THE SAND AND PLAY GAMES
ON THE PIER.

06:10.239 --> 06:11.893
WALK WITH PEOPLE IN VENICE.

06:12.546 --> 06:15.113
OH, PLEASE, JAMES,
TAKE ME THERE.

06:16.201 --> 06:18.639
-IF YOUR FATHER APPROVES.

06:19.291 --> 06:21.903
-NO.
-BUT WHY NOT?

06:22.033 --> 06:25.646
-BECAUSE SUNNING YOURSELF
ON A PUBLIC BEACH IS
NOT APPROPRIATE.

06:25.776 --> 06:28.083
-FATHER,
NOTHING'S EVER APPROPRIATE.

06:28.213 --> 06:32.304
I'M BORED. I JUST WANT
TO HAVE FUN IN THE REAL WORLD,

06:32.435 --> 06:34.002
AT LEAST FOR A FEW HOURS.

06:34.916 --> 06:36.744
-TRUST ME.

06:36.874 --> 06:39.355
YOU WOULD NOT LIKE HOT DOGS
BETTER THAN PHEASANT.

06:40.138 --> 06:41.531
-I WOULDN'T KNOW.

06:41.662 --> 06:43.838
I'VE NEVER TASTED A HOT DOG.

06:57.373 --> 06:59.897
-A WEEK AND THE PRINCESS HASN'T
SET FOOT OFF LEWISTON'S YACHT.

07:00.898 --> 07:03.118
-WE'VE GOT TO BE READY
IF AND WHEN SHE DOES.

07:16.610 --> 07:18.525
-YEAH.
-HOW DOES IT LOOK, TOM?

07:18.655 --> 07:20.222
-YOU STILL GOT A SHOT, BEN.

07:20.352 --> 07:21.963
YOUR BOAT'S IN THIRD
BY SIX SECONDS.

07:22.659 --> 07:24.487
-YOU'LL LET ME KNOW
IF ANYTHING CHANGES?

07:41.330 --> 07:44.855
-MITCH, BEFORE YOU SAY ANYTHING,
I AM SO SORRY.

07:44.986 --> 07:46.901
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING SURF SKIING
TODAY?

07:47.031 --> 07:48.729
YOU KNEW THE TIME TRIALS
WERE HAPPENING.

07:48.859 --> 07:51.296
-I JUST GOT OFF A 24-HOUR SHIFT.
I FORGOT WHAT DAY IT WAS.

07:51.427 --> 07:52.950
-[GROANS]
-I'M SORRY.

07:53.603 --> 07:56.301
-IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY. WE'RE NOT
OUT OF THE RUNNING YET.

07:56.954 --> 07:57.868
-YES, WE ARE.

08:00.175 --> 08:03.047
-WE JUST FINISHED FOURTH
BY 2 1/2 LOUSY SECONDS.

08:03.178 --> 08:04.745
-WHAT DID THE COMMITTEE SAY?

08:04.875 --> 08:06.834
-THEY WON'T HEAR OUR PROTEST.

08:06.964 --> 08:09.401
-THAT LEWISTON, HE'S PRETTY
TIGHT WITH THE ROYAL FAMILY.

08:09.532 --> 08:10.968
HELL, THEY'RE STAYING
ON HIS YACHT.

08:11.099 --> 08:12.535
-WELL, YOU'LL WIN NEXT YEAR.

08:12.666 --> 08:14.972
-THERE'S NOT GOING TO
BE ANY NEXT YEAR, DEAR.

08:17.192 --> 08:20.108
HELL, IT'S ALL ONE BIG
PIPE DREAM ANYWAY.

08:25.853 --> 08:27.898
-NO FINALS, NO SPONSOR.

08:29.421 --> 08:31.032
NO SPONSOR, NO BOAT.

08:35.775 --> 08:36.951
-THANK YOU.

08:38.082 --> 08:40.041
-HAVE YOU RECEIVED ANY FURTHER
INTELLIGENCE?

08:40.171 --> 08:41.433
-ONLY RUMORS, YOUR HIGHNESS,

08:42.086 --> 08:44.001
BUT AS YOUR CHIEF OF SECURITY,
LET ME ASSURE YOU

08:44.131 --> 08:46.134
THAT NO ONE WOULD DARE KIDNAP
THE PRINCESS CATHERINE HERE.

08:47.831 --> 08:50.660
THESE SORT OF RUMORS ARE NEVER
TO BE TAKEN LIGHTLY, ROLAND.

08:51.313 --> 08:52.923
UNTIL WE'RE ABSOLUTELY SURE,

08:53.054 --> 08:55.883
I WANT MY DAUGHTER PROTECTED
AT ALL TIMES.

10:03.951 --> 10:05.735
-HELP ME!

10:27.583 --> 10:30.934
[COUGHING]

10:31.065 --> 10:32.849
-ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
YOU ALL RIGHT?

10:33.589 --> 10:36.418
-NOW I AM.
-OKAY. HANG ON.

10:37.245 --> 10:40.161
HANG ON. HERE WE GO.
OKAY. OKAY.

10:48.473 --> 10:51.607
YOU ALL RIGHT?
-[COUGHS]

10:51.738 --> 10:54.218
MY NAME IS MITCH BUCHANNON.
I'M AN L.A. COUNTY LIFEGUARD.

10:57.308 --> 10:58.396
HAVE WE MET?

10:59.136 --> 11:01.486
-NO. I WOULD REMEMBER.

11:02.749 --> 11:04.489
THANK YOU FOR RESCUING ME,
MITCH BUCHANNON.

11:05.752 --> 11:07.710
MY NAME IS CA--CATHY.

11:09.799 --> 11:13.455
-ANY TIME. YOU WITH SOME
FRIENDS AROUND HERE?

11:13.585 --> 11:15.762
-NO. NO, I CAME ALONE.

11:17.546 --> 11:18.852
-HERE.

11:20.027 --> 11:23.291
THERE YOU GO. COME ON.
I'LL HELP YOU FIND YOUR THINGS.

11:26.033 --> 11:28.905
-I'M SURE I LEFT MY TOWEL
AROUND HERE SOMEPLACE.

11:29.645 --> 11:31.691
-WELL, THE OCEAN CAN CARRY YOU
PRETTY FAR.

11:31.821 --> 11:33.344
-NO, NO. IT WAS HERE.

11:33.475 --> 11:36.086
I REMEMBER STATION 15.

11:37.827 --> 11:39.786
MY THINGS MUST HAVE BEEN STOLEN.

11:39.916 --> 11:41.396
-YOU WANT TO FILE A REPORT?

11:41.526 --> 11:44.181
-NO! NO. THERE WAS NOTHING
OF ANY REAL VALUE.

11:44.834 --> 11:46.749
-WHAT ABOUT YOUR WALLET
OR YOUR KEYS?

11:47.489 --> 11:49.099
-MY FRIENDS DROPPED ME
OFF HERE.

11:49.230 --> 11:50.405
-OH.

11:51.580 --> 11:53.495
-I'M AFRAID I'M STRANDED.

11:54.409 --> 11:56.890
-WELL, I CAN DRIVE YOU HOME.
MY SHIFT DOESN'T START
TILL 3:00.

11:57.020 --> 11:58.326
I MEAN, WHERE DO YOU LIVE?

11:58.456 --> 12:00.763
-I'M VISITING.
I'M STAYING WITH FRIENDS.

12:01.285 --> 12:03.157
I'M AFRAID THEY WON'T BE THERE.

12:04.767 --> 12:06.769
-WELL, I CAN'T LEAVE YOU
STRANDED NOW, CAN I?

12:08.510 --> 12:10.773
I MEAN, THERE'S GOTTA BE
SOMETHING I CAN DO FOR YOU.

12:22.742 --> 12:25.005
-MMM. DON'T LET LOOKS FOOL YOU.

12:25.135 --> 12:27.442
HE MAKES THE BEST HOT DOGS
IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA.

12:27.572 --> 12:29.487
-WHAT DO YOU WANT ON YOURS?
-EVERYTHING.

12:29.618 --> 12:33.753
-LOU, GIVE ME A COUPLE VENICE
DOGS WITH THE WORKS AND PEPSI?

12:33.883 --> 12:35.319
-PEPSI.
-AND A WATER.

12:36.407 --> 12:39.236
SO UM... WHAT BRINGS
YOU TO CALIFORNIA?

12:39.933 --> 12:41.499
BUSINESS? PLEASURE?
-PLEASURE.

12:42.283 --> 12:43.371
AS MUCH AS I CAN SQUEEZE IN.

12:45.155 --> 12:47.723
-WHERE YOU FROM?
-FAR AWAY.

12:48.463 --> 12:52.423
NO BEACHES, NO OCEANS,
NOTHING AS MARVELOUS AS THIS.

12:53.816 --> 12:55.775
-THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
-YEAH, YOU GOT IT.

12:55.905 --> 12:58.125
-OKAY, NOW, BE CAREFUL,
THEY'RE REAL MESSY.

13:00.475 --> 13:03.739
-MMM! MMM, IT'S DIVINE.

13:03.870 --> 13:05.393
-[LAUGHS]

13:05.959 --> 13:08.788
-I LOVE IT HERE.
THERE'S SO MUCH LIFE.

13:09.397 --> 13:13.096
-WELL, THE WAVES ARE LIKE
A NATURAL PULSE, YOU KNOW?

13:13.227 --> 13:14.750
REMINDS PEOPLE
THAT THEY'RE ALIVE.

13:15.359 --> 13:16.839
-THERE'S A POET IN YOU,
MITCH BUCHANNON.

13:16.970 --> 13:18.798
-YEAH, YEAH, I KNOW, I KNOW...
A BAD POET.

13:18.928 --> 13:20.582
WAIT A SECOND, YOU HAVE
A LITTLE STUFF RIGHT THERE.

13:21.235 --> 13:22.323
-HMM.

13:23.803 --> 13:25.326
-HEY!

13:27.676 --> 13:29.460
-I'M AFRAID I HAVEN'T ANY MONEY,

13:30.070 --> 13:31.941
BUT I'LL GIVE YOU THIS
IN EXCHANGE FOR THESE CLOTHES.

13:32.072 --> 13:35.205
-IT'S 24-CARAT GOLD.
-RIGHT.

13:35.336 --> 13:37.512
YOU'RE GOING TO EXCHANGE THIS
GOLD BRACELET FOR CLOTHES?

13:38.252 --> 13:39.601
-I'M SORRY, IT'S ALL I HAVE.

13:39.731 --> 13:41.211
-WAIT A MINUTE, WAIT A MINUTE.

13:41.342 --> 13:42.560
I'LL PAY FOR THE CLOTHES.
HOW MUCH ARE THEY?

13:42.691 --> 13:43.910
-$8.

13:45.781 --> 13:47.827
-THEN YOU MUST TAKE THIS.
-NO, NO, NO.

13:47.957 --> 13:50.438
THERE'S AN OLD CHINESE SAYING.
"WHEN YOU RESCUE SOMEONE
FROM DROWNING,

13:50.568 --> 13:52.919
YOU MUST PROVIDE THEM
WITH DRY CLOTHES."

13:53.049 --> 13:56.183
-WELL, THERE'S A SAYING WHERE I
COME FROM THAT IF SOMEBODY
SAVES YOU FROM DROWNING,

13:56.313 --> 13:58.446
YOU MUST GIVE THEM
SOMETHING WET.

14:02.276 --> 14:03.886
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU CAN'T FIND HER?

14:04.017 --> 14:06.062
-WE'VE CHECKED EVERY INCH
OF THE SHIP.

14:07.411 --> 14:08.891
I'M SORRY, YOUR MAJESTY.

14:09.022 --> 14:10.719
I'VE NO IDEA HOW THIS
COULD HAVE HAPPENED.

14:11.720 --> 14:13.809
-WE MUST INFORM THE COAST GUARD
AND THE LOCAL POLICE.

14:14.549 --> 14:18.205
-YOUR HIGHNESS, IF I MAY,
I THINK IT BETTER IF I SEARCH
WITH MY OWN MEN.

14:18.814 --> 14:21.382
CONTACTING THE POLICE WOULD
CERTAINLY MEAN INVOLVING
THE PRESS,

14:22.078 --> 14:24.994
AND IF IT BECAME KNOWN THAT
THE PRINCESS CATHERINE
WAS LEFT UNGUARDED--

14:26.256 --> 14:28.432
-[SIGHS]
YES, I SEE YOUR POINT.

14:28.563 --> 14:31.348
-WELL, I DON'T.
-JAMES.

14:32.132 --> 14:34.525
I HAVEN'T SAID ANYTHING
TO YOU OR TO CATHERINE.

14:35.483 --> 14:37.050
I DIDN'T WISH TO ALARM
EITHER ONE OF YOU.

14:38.268 --> 14:41.358
BUT THERE ARE RUMORS THAT
AN EXTREMIST GROUP MAY TRY

14:41.489 --> 14:44.884
TO KIDNAP CATHERINE IN ORDER
TO EXCHANGE HER FOR
CERTAIN MEMBERS

14:45.014 --> 14:49.671
OF THEIR ORGANIZATION
WHO ARE BEING HELD
IN OUR PRISONS.

14:52.543 --> 14:56.156
-DAD! DAD, GUESS WHAT.

14:56.808 --> 14:58.288
WHOA!

14:58.854 --> 15:00.900
THE RACE COMMITTEE DECIDED
TO HEAR OUR PROTEST.

15:01.030 --> 15:03.554
-GREAT! I WAS IN
A BOAT RACE YESTERDAY,

15:03.685 --> 15:04.947
AND WE'RE CHALLENGING
THE RESULTS.

15:05.078 --> 15:06.427
-I'M SURE YOU'RE IN THE RIGHT.

15:07.471 --> 15:10.039
I HAVE NEVER SEEN SKATES
LIKE THESE BEFORE.

15:10.170 --> 15:11.345
-THEY'RE ROLLERBLADES.

15:11.954 --> 15:13.956
-CATHY, THIS IS MY SON, HOBIE.
HOBIE, THIS IS CATHY.

15:14.087 --> 15:15.566
-PLEASED TO MEET YOU, HOBIE.
-ME, TOO.

15:15.697 --> 15:17.699
BEN WANTS YOU TO MEET HIM
AT THE BOAT RIGHT AWAY.

15:17.829 --> 15:20.963
-OKAY.
WHY DON'T YOU COME WITH US?

15:21.094 --> 15:22.530
WE CAN CALL YOUR FRIENDS
FROM THERE.

15:22.660 --> 15:23.792
-MY FRIENDS?
-YEAH.

15:23.923 --> 15:25.968
-OH, RIGHT. YES, I'LL CALL.

15:26.099 --> 15:27.665
-THANK YOU.
LET'S DO IT.

15:27.796 --> 15:29.363
-YOUR HIGHNESS, THE PRINCESS.

15:32.583 --> 15:34.455
-CATHERINE, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

15:34.585 --> 15:38.328
-I'M FINE. I TOLD YOU I WANTED
TO COME TO THE BEACH, AND I DID.

15:38.459 --> 15:40.983
-WHERE ON THE BEACH?
I'LL TELL ROLAND.

15:41.114 --> 15:43.943
-I'M NOT READY TO COME BACK YET.
-CATHERINE...

15:44.073 --> 15:45.814
-FATHER, PLEASE LISTEN TO ME.

15:45.945 --> 15:48.425
I WAS BORN YOUR DAUGHTER,
AND SOON I'LL BE JAMES' WIFE,

15:48.556 --> 15:50.732
AND I'VE HAD NO SAY
IN EITHER DECISION.

15:50.862 --> 15:53.996
THIS IS MY LAST CHANCE TO DO
SOMETHING FOR MYSELF,
AND I'M TAKING IT.

15:54.605 --> 15:57.391
-CATHERINE, YOU DON'T
UNDERSTAND THE DANGER.

15:57.521 --> 16:00.785
-I'LL TELL YOU WHEN TO PICK ME
UP WHEN I'M READY, NOT BEFORE.

16:15.931 --> 16:17.715
-TELL ROLAND I NEED
TO SEE HIM AT ONCE.

16:20.066 --> 16:22.459
-MAN, THIS WAITING
IS KILLING ME.

16:23.199 --> 16:24.418
-I'M SURE BEN WILL BE HERE SOON.

16:25.201 --> 16:26.724
-I'M GOING TO GIVE THIS
ENGINE A ONCE-OVER.

16:26.855 --> 16:28.248
HOBE, YOU WANT TO LAY SOME
NEWSPAPER OUT FOR ME?

16:28.378 --> 16:29.989
-YEAH, SURE.
-ALL RIGHT.

16:31.425 --> 16:32.774
-HEY.
-HI.

16:33.427 --> 16:35.081
-DID YOU GET AHOLD
OF YOUR FRIENDS?

16:35.211 --> 16:37.170
-NO, THEY'RE STILL NOT THERE,
BUT I LEFT A MESSAGE.

16:46.962 --> 16:51.271
-"PRINCESS CATHERINE TO PRESENT
RANDENBERG CUP."

16:53.186 --> 16:56.276
OW!
-ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

16:56.928 --> 16:58.974
-GOT TO BE A LITTLE BIT MORE
CAREFUL THERE, SPORT.

17:06.329 --> 17:07.678
-HOLY COW!

17:11.943 --> 17:15.859
-COME SKATING WITH ME.
-I CAN'T, I CAN'T.
I GOT TO WAIT FOR BEN.

17:15.991 --> 17:17.688
OUR SHIFT STARTS
IN JUST A FEW MINUTES.

17:18.298 --> 17:20.778
-I'LL TAKE HER, THEN YOU GUYS
CAN DO SOMETHING TOGETHER
AFTER WORK.

17:20.909 --> 17:24.173
-AH, I'D LOVE THAT.
-ALL RIGHT, HAVE FUN.

17:24.304 --> 17:25.521
-ALL RIGHT, SEE YOU.
-BE CAREFUL.

17:25.653 --> 17:26.696
-I WILL.
-OKAY.

17:30.832 --> 17:33.139
-WHOO! WHOO!

17:34.966 --> 17:36.664
-[EXHALES]

17:45.586 --> 17:46.891
-[GASPS]

17:47.022 --> 17:49.416
-SORRY.
-COME ON, I'VE JUST SEEN HER.

17:49.546 --> 17:53.028
-WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?!
OOH! JERKS!

18:03.169 --> 18:04.300
-WHEE!

18:05.040 --> 18:07.086
-THERE.
-WHOO!

18:37.986 --> 18:41.207
-[GASPS] HEY!
-[GRUNTING]

18:41.859 --> 18:43.165
-WHOA!

19:14.631 --> 19:16.807
-WHOA! HEY! HEY! CAREFUL!

19:25.294 --> 19:28.428
-[GRUNTS]
-UGH!

19:40.788 --> 19:42.964
-WHOA!
-THANK YOU, HOBIE.

19:43.094 --> 19:45.836
-WE GOT TO GET BACK TO MY DAD
AND TELL HIM WHO YOU REALLY ARE.

19:46.533 --> 19:47.534
-YOU KNOW WHO I AM?

19:49.231 --> 19:50.232
-YOU'RE A PRINCESS.

19:51.102 --> 19:52.539
-DOES YOUR FATHER KNOW?

19:52.669 --> 19:54.410
-NO. I FIGURED IF I
TOLD HIM, HE'D FREAK.

19:55.368 --> 19:56.499
-PLEASE DON'T TELL HIM.

19:57.587 --> 20:00.547
-BUT THOSE GUYS.
YOU COULD BE IN DANGER.

20:01.156 --> 20:04.246
-NO, NO. THEY WERE JUST
ASSIGNED TO PROTECT ME.

20:04.377 --> 20:05.595
THEY WANT TO BRING ME BACK.

20:06.248 --> 20:08.946
HAVEN'T YOU EVER JUST WANTED
TO BE ON YOUR OWN

20:09.077 --> 20:10.557
WITHOUT ANYBODY TELLING YOU
WHAT TO DO?

20:10.687 --> 20:11.949
-OF COURSE I HAVE... I'M A KID.

20:12.080 --> 20:14.430
-THEN YOU KNOW EXACTLY
HOW I FEEL.

20:14.996 --> 20:16.171
PROMISE ME YOU WON'T TELL HIM.

20:16.998 --> 20:18.260
-BUT YOU CAN TRUST MY DAD.

20:19.000 --> 20:20.436
-I KNOW I CAN, BUT...

20:21.002 --> 20:23.134
IF HE KNOWS WHO I AM,
HE'LL FREAK, AS YOU SAY,

20:23.265 --> 20:26.225
AND THAT MIGHT SPOIL EVERYTHING.
PLEASE.

20:30.794 --> 20:33.710
-OKAY, I PROMISE.
-OH, THANK YOU.

20:44.199 --> 20:47.594
-LOOKS LIKE THEY'RE CONDONING
LEWISTON FOR ALMOST RUNNING
C.J. DOWN.

20:49.204 --> 20:53.730
-MITCH, HIS BOAT NEVER
TOUCHED HER OR HER SKI.

20:54.340 --> 20:56.298
THERE'S NO HARM, NO FOUL.

20:56.429 --> 20:57.821
-CAN'T WE APPEAL THIS THING?

20:58.605 --> 21:00.737
NO.
THERE'S NOBODY TO APPEAL TO.

21:01.390 --> 21:03.262
THE RACE COMMITTEE'S
DECISION'S FINAL.

21:04.480 --> 21:08.136
YOU KNOW, I HAD A LOT
OF DREAMS IN MY DAY.

21:08.745 --> 21:12.227
RUNNING A BOAT LIKE THIS--

21:14.273 --> 21:15.535
THAT WAS ONE OF THEM.

21:17.363 --> 21:18.581
I'M TRYING TO REMEMBER

21:18.712 --> 21:22.716
WHAT ALL THOSE OTHER
DREAMS WERE,

21:23.630 --> 21:24.761
AND I CAN'T.

21:26.850 --> 21:29.070
I STARTED GETTING OLD
SOME PLACE.

21:32.595 --> 21:33.944
OH, GOD.

21:34.075 --> 21:35.772
LISTEN TO ME, GUYS, WILL YOU?

21:36.295 --> 21:39.689
YOU TWO TAKE OFF.
I WANT TO BE LEFT ALONE.

21:41.474 --> 21:43.345
-ALL RIGHT, WE'LL LEAVE
YOU BY YOURSELF,

21:43.867 --> 21:46.653
BUT YOU ARE NEVER ALONE.

22:02.190 --> 22:04.105
-IT JUST DOESN'T SEEM FAIR.

22:04.235 --> 22:07.108
YOU SHOULDN'T BE PENALIZED
BECAUSE SOMEONE WAS
ALMOST INJURED.

22:07.238 --> 22:08.718
-WELL, WHEN IT'S
THE RANDENBERG CUP,

22:08.849 --> 22:10.764
AND YOU'RE FRIENDS
WITH THE RANDENBERGS,

22:10.894 --> 22:13.201
FAIR DOESN'T ENTER INTO IT.

22:13.723 --> 22:16.073
-THANK YOU. I SHOULD CALL
MY FRIENDS.

22:16.204 --> 22:18.685
MAY I USE YOUR PHONE?
-BOTH: SURE, IT'S IN THE DEN.

22:18.815 --> 22:20.339
-THANK YOU.
-WHY, I OUGHTA...

22:22.819 --> 22:24.517
-HAAGEN-DAZS.
-HAAGEN-DAZS?

22:24.647 --> 22:26.388
-YEAH. DIDN'T DO YOUR HOMEWORK
LAST NIGHT, DID YOU?

22:26.519 --> 22:27.650
-AW, MAN.

22:28.390 --> 22:29.870
-SO YOU REALLY LIKE HER,
HUH, DAD?

22:30.000 --> 22:32.438
-SURE. GIVE ME A BREAK.
WHAT'S NOT TO LIKE?

22:32.568 --> 22:34.483
-I GOT A GREAT IDEA.
LET'S MAKE A FIRE!

22:34.614 --> 22:36.790
-HEY, IT'S THE MIDDLE
OF THE SUMMER.

22:37.704 --> 22:39.793
-YOU'LL SEE. IT'S KIND OF
COOL TONIGHT, ANYWAY.

22:39.923 --> 22:42.622
I'LL OPEN SOME WINDOWS.
WE HAVEN'T HAD A FIRE IN MONTHS.

22:43.362 --> 22:44.624
-HEY! HEY!

22:47.453 --> 22:49.324
-YES.
THIS IS PRINCESS CATHERINE.

22:49.455 --> 22:51.413
I'D LIKE TO SPEAK
TO THE CHAIRMAN OF
THE RACE COMMITTEE.

22:56.897 --> 22:59.290
-ANY LUCK?
-THEY'RE STILL NOT HOME.

22:59.943 --> 23:01.336
THANK YOU FOR LETTING ME
STAY HERE.

23:01.467 --> 23:03.817
-MY PLEASURE.
-HEY, WE MADE A FIRE.

23:04.383 --> 23:06.646
-LOVELY.
BUT ISN'T IT A BIT WARM?

23:06.776 --> 23:08.299
-APPARENTLY NOT.

23:10.693 --> 23:12.782
HOBIE, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

23:13.479 --> 23:15.785
-JUST THOUGHT I'D TURN DOWN
THE LIGHTS SO WE COULD
SEE THE FIRE BETTER.

23:16.438 --> 23:20.268
[YAWNS] BESIDES,
I'M... I'M BUSHED.

23:20.399 --> 23:21.835
I THINK I'LL HIT THE SACK.

23:21.965 --> 23:23.793
YOU GUYS, JUST STAY UP
AS LATE AS YOU WANT.

23:23.924 --> 23:26.317
MAYBE I'LL READ THE DICTIONARY
OR SOMETHING.

23:28.015 --> 23:30.017
GOOD NIGHT.
-BOTH: GOOD NIGHT.

23:31.453 --> 23:33.716
-HE USUALLY GOES TO BED
KICKING AND SCREAMING.

23:34.848 --> 23:37.198
OBVIOUSLY, YOU'VE MADE QUITE
AN IMPRESSION ON HIM.

23:37.894 --> 23:40.462
-HIS FATHER'S MADE QUITE
AN IMPRESSION ON ME.

23:57.174 --> 23:58.524
-MAY I HAVE ANOTHER, PLEASE?

24:00.090 --> 24:02.223
-YOU REALIZE WE'VE BEEN
TOGETHER ALL DAY,

24:02.832 --> 24:06.357
AND ALL I KNOW ABOUT YOU
IS THAT YOU LOVE HOT DOGS
AND ROOT BEER FLOATS?

24:06.488 --> 24:08.969
-I THINK IT'S WONDERFUL YOU
AND GAYLE REMAIN FRIENDS.

24:09.099 --> 24:11.319
-SEE, THERE YOU GO CHANGING
THE SUBJECT AGAIN.

24:13.016 --> 24:16.019
-I'VE NEVER BEEN
A MYSTERY WOMAN. IT'S FUN.

24:16.150 --> 24:18.500
-YEAH, I KNOW, BUT I WANT
TO KNOW MORE ABOUT YOU.

24:19.414 --> 24:22.896
-PEOPLE WHO KNOW ME THINK
MY LIFE IS A FAIRY TALE,
BUT IT'S NOT.

24:24.027 --> 24:26.465
THIS IS MY FAIRY TALE,
HERE WITH YOU.

24:27.378 --> 24:29.119
I DON'T WANT TO BREAK THE SPELL.

24:45.048 --> 24:48.138
-[PRETEND FIGHTING]

24:53.666 --> 24:56.495
FOR RESCUING MY DAUGHTER
AND OTHER ACTS OF BRAVERY,

24:56.625 --> 24:59.236
I KNIGHT YOU SIR HOBIE,

24:59.367 --> 25:01.587
ORDER OF MOST
EXCELLENT HEROES

25:01.717 --> 25:04.198
AND FUTURE HEIR
TO MY ROYAL THRONE.

25:04.328 --> 25:05.982
YEAH!

25:40.364 --> 25:44.455
♪ I FEEL THAT I'M AWAKE
♪ INSIDE THIS DREAM

25:48.677 --> 25:52.594
♪ AND THIS IS THE WAY IT'S MEANT TO BE

25:53.552 --> 25:56.859
♪ I'LL KEEP REACHING FOR THE SKY

25:56.990 --> 25:59.993
♪ I KNOW THE SUN WILL SHINE

26:00.733 --> 26:05.476
♪ AND THE WIND WILL CARRY ME AWAY ♪

26:06.042 --> 26:09.306
♪ TO THE END OF TIME ♪

26:10.177 --> 26:14.007
♪ THIS IS ALWAYS IN MY MIND

26:14.137 --> 26:17.532
♪ NOW IT'S COME INTO MY LIFE

26:18.054 --> 26:22.537
♪ HOW CAN THIS DREAM THAT LAST FOREVER ♪

26:23.233 --> 26:26.106
♪ FOREVER FLYING HIGH

26:26.236 --> 26:31.372
♪ AS LONG AS IT TAKES
♪ TO BRING IT TOGETHER

26:33.243 --> 26:36.943
♪ I CAN SEE THE SUN IS RISIN'

26:37.073 --> 26:41.077
♪ A NEW DAY HAS COME TO LIFE

26:41.208 --> 26:44.733
♪ SO CARRY ME AWAY

26:44.864 --> 26:49.259
♪ 'CAUSE I BELIEVE, OH YEAH

26:49.390 --> 26:51.784
♪ IN THIS DREAM

26:55.701 --> 27:00.575
♪ HOW CAN THIS DREAM THAT LAST FOREVER

27:00.706 --> 27:03.796
♪ FOREVER FLYING HIGH

27:03.926 --> 27:08.975
♪ AS LONG AS IT TAKES
♪ TO BRING IT TOGETHER

27:10.890 --> 27:14.241
♪ I CAN SEE THE SUN IS RISIN'

27:14.981 --> 27:18.462
♪ A NEW DAY HAS COME TO LIFE ♪

27:18.593 --> 27:22.249
♪ SO CARRY ME AWAY

27:22.379 --> 27:25.556
♪ 'CAUSE I BELIEVE

27:26.862 --> 27:29.212
♪ IN THIS DREAM

27:47.274 --> 27:48.971
-[LAUGHING]

27:50.233 --> 27:53.062
-HEY, WHOA, WHOA,
STOP THAT, THAT TICKLES.

27:53.193 --> 27:54.890
-I'M SORRY.

27:57.284 --> 27:58.938
WELL, I'M GOING FOR A SWIM NOW.

28:00.504 --> 28:02.463
-YOU'LL PAY FOR THIS.

28:02.593 --> 28:05.031
-WELL, YOU HAVE SUCH A HANDSOME
FACE, YOU DON'T NEED
A BODY ANYWAY.

28:05.161 --> 28:07.903
-AW, DON'T LEAVE ME HERE.
I'LL RESCUE YOU.

28:09.949 --> 28:12.125
-ALL RIGHT, CATHERINE,
YOU'VE HAD YOUR FUN.

28:12.255 --> 28:15.781
NOW IT'S TIME TO GO HOME.
-I WILL RETURN WHEN I'M READY!

28:16.869 --> 28:18.435
LET GO OF ME!

28:20.524 --> 28:22.048
-WHO IS THIS CREEP ANYWAY?

28:22.178 --> 28:24.528
-HE WORKS FOR MY FATHER.
HE WANTS TO BRING ME BACK.

28:24.659 --> 28:26.356
BUT I WON'T GO, NOT YET.

28:27.967 --> 28:31.057
WILL YOU HOLD HIM HERE, PLEASE,
UNTIL I'M GONE? I'M SORRY.

28:34.408 --> 28:37.367
-COME NEAR HER AGAIN,
I'LL HAVE YOU ARRESTED.

29:10.531 --> 29:11.924
-YOUR HIGHNESS.
-YES.

29:12.054 --> 29:14.230
-I'M AFRAID THERE'S
NOTHING NEW TO REPORT.

29:14.361 --> 29:16.406
I'M STILL UNABLE
TO LOCATE THE PRINCESS.

29:16.929 --> 29:19.975
IF IT'S OF ANY COMFORT, SIR,
I DOUBT IF SHE'S IN DANGER.

29:20.846 --> 29:22.586
EVEN IF A DOMESTIC PLOT
DOES EXIST,

29:22.717 --> 29:25.328
IT'S UNLIKELY
TO UNFOLD THIS FAR FROM HOME.

29:38.602 --> 29:41.867
-YOU WERE RIGHT. HE WAS PILOTING
ONE OF THE BOATS.

29:43.651 --> 29:45.305
HIS NAME IS MITCH BUCHANNON.

29:46.436 --> 29:47.786
HE'S A LIFEGUARD.

29:49.135 --> 29:50.484
-ALL RIGHT.

29:50.614 --> 29:52.181
WE GO TOMORROW AS PLANNED.

29:53.356 --> 29:54.662
AND THIS TIME...

29:57.230 --> 29:58.405
NO SURPRISES.

30:13.463 --> 30:15.074
-[KNOCK ON DOOR]

30:25.084 --> 30:27.477
-MITCH, PLEASE UNDERSTAND.

30:28.304 --> 30:30.611
IF I TELL YOU EVERYTHING,
WE MIGHT LOSE WHAT WE
FOUND HERE TOGETHER.

30:30.741 --> 30:33.222
-WELL, WE'RE DEFINITELY GOING TO
LOSE WHAT WE FOUND HERE

30:33.353 --> 30:34.745
IF WE CAN'T BE HONEST
WITH EACH OTHER.

30:39.446 --> 30:40.882
-I'M ENGAGED TO BE MARRIED.

30:41.796 --> 30:44.233
MY FATHER'S PLANNING TO ANNOUNCE
MY ENGAGEMENT TOMORROW.

30:47.019 --> 30:48.150
-WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

30:49.195 --> 30:50.326
-I DIDN'T WANT TO LOSE YOU.

30:50.936 --> 30:52.328
-YEAH, BUT YOU'RE GETTING
MARRIED.

30:52.459 --> 30:53.895
-I DON'T LOVE HIM.

30:54.940 --> 30:56.550
-THEN WHY ARE YOU MARRYING HIM?

30:58.030 --> 31:00.206
-MY FATHER, MY FAMILY.

31:02.121 --> 31:03.774
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT I WAS GIVING UP.

31:04.863 --> 31:07.126
I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT LOVE WAS.

31:09.693 --> 31:11.086
TILL NOW.

31:11.217 --> 31:12.958
-OH.

31:28.582 --> 31:29.931
MORNING.

31:32.803 --> 31:37.286
-MITCH! I HAVE BEEN LEAVING
MESSAGES FOR YOU EVERYWHERE.
-WHAT'S UP?

31:37.417 --> 31:40.855
-TOM FROM THE RACE COMMITTEE
CAME BY TO SEE BEN, AND IT
LOOKS LIKE THE ROYAL FAMILY

31:40.986 --> 31:42.552
GOT THEM TO RECONSIDER
YOUR PROTEST.

31:42.683 --> 31:44.032
-AND?
-YOU'RE IN!

31:44.163 --> 31:45.816
-YES! YES!

31:45.947 --> 31:47.949
YOU, LEWISTON AND ANOTHER BOAT
IN A THREE-WAY FINAL.

31:48.080 --> 31:49.559
-FANTASTIC!

32:22.505 --> 32:26.466
♪ KING OF

32:28.120 --> 32:33.516
♪ A THOUSAND TIDES

32:52.666 --> 32:54.407
♪ LET'S GO

32:55.016 --> 32:58.063
♪ DREAMING IN DOUBLE TIME ♪

33:00.891 --> 33:02.937
♪ WE'LL THROW

33:03.068 --> 33:06.332
♪ CAUTION TO WINDS BEHIND

33:08.856 --> 33:11.119
♪ LIVE FAST

33:11.250 --> 33:14.253
♪ DANGER CAN CHANGE THE GAME

33:17.082 --> 33:18.822
♪ UNMASK

33:19.475 --> 33:22.870
♪ THE HUNGER TO TAME THE WAVES ♪

33:25.220 --> 33:29.833
♪ HOLD ON, THE WIND
♪ AND SEA WILL GUIDE YOU

33:33.141 --> 33:38.712
♪ DON'T STOP, MOVING THE SPEED OF LIGHT

33:40.888 --> 33:46.241
♪ SO STAND STRONG
♪ THE BRAVEST HEART INSIDE YOU

33:49.549 --> 33:55.120
♪ WILL BE CROWNED
♪ KING OF A THOUSAND TIDES

33:57.731 --> 33:59.472
-ALL RIGHT, CATHERINE.

33:59.602 --> 34:02.083
-BOTH BOATS ARE FULL THROTTLE
AS THEY APPROACH THE TURN.

34:03.693 --> 34:06.870
-THAT'S ENOUGH, ROLAND.
TELL MY FATHER I'LL RETURN
AFTER THE RACE.

34:07.001 --> 34:08.524
-I DON'T THINK SO,
YOUR HIGHNESS.

34:09.047 --> 34:12.789
-HAVE YOU LOST YOUR MIND?
-NO, NOT AT ALL.

34:12.920 --> 34:14.704
CONSIDER THIS A CAREER MOVE.

34:14.835 --> 34:18.056
I'M SURE YOUR FIANCE WILL FIND
$10 MILLION A REASONABLE RANSOM.

34:18.186 --> 34:19.579
-YOU'RE KIDNAPPING ME?

34:20.623 --> 34:23.190
-YES. ACTUALLY, YES.

34:23.844 --> 34:25.367
BUT THE BLAME WILL FALL
ON THE EXTREMISTS,

34:25.498 --> 34:27.021
AT LEAST UNTIL WE DISAPPEAR.

34:29.415 --> 34:31.982
-CATHY!
-ANNOUNCER: BUCHANNON
TAKES THE LEAD.

34:32.112 --> 34:33.288
-HOBIE, BE CAREFUL!

34:35.551 --> 34:36.422
HOBIE!

34:39.773 --> 34:42.949
HOBIE!
CALL THE POLICE, HOBIE!

34:51.001 --> 34:54.396
-COME ON, MITCH!
SQUEEZE HIM! SQUEEZE HIM!

35:07.235 --> 35:09.759
COME ON, MITCH!
GO ALL THE WAY! SQUEEZE HIM!

35:20.466 --> 35:22.685
-YES!
-YEAH!

35:22.816 --> 35:26.341
-I JUST HEARD FROM BEN.
CATHY'S BEEN KIDNAPPED.
-WHAT?

35:26.472 --> 35:28.213
-THEY'RE HEADING NORTH
IN A GRAY CHAPARRAL.

35:28.343 --> 35:30.650
-LET'S GO.
-HEY, MITCH,
WE DON'T HAVE ENOUGH FUEL.

35:31.303 --> 35:33.043
-WE'LL GO IN THIS.
COME ON, MITCH.

35:57.720 --> 36:00.549
-TURN TOWARD THEM!
-WHAT?

36:00.680 --> 36:03.596
-TURN TOWARD THEM!
WE'LL NEVER OUTRUN THEM! TURN!

36:11.125 --> 36:13.867
-WHAT'S HE DOING?
-GET DOWN!

36:19.873 --> 36:21.353
ALL RIGHT, TURN AROUND.
-ARE YOU NUTS?

36:21.483 --> 36:22.310
JUST DO IT, HUH?

36:46.595 --> 36:48.902
-[GRUNTS, SCREAMS]

36:58.433 --> 36:59.869
-STOP THE BOAT!

37:04.004 --> 37:05.310
-OKAY, CALL FOR BACKUP.

37:06.789 --> 37:08.226
-"SCARAB" TO HEADQUARTERS.

37:17.713 --> 37:19.672
-FISH HIM OUT, HUH?
-YOU GOT IT.

37:20.281 --> 37:22.152
-YOU ALL RIGHT?
-NOW I AM.

37:23.241 --> 37:25.939
-[SIREN WAILING]

37:43.173 --> 37:46.394
-DAD.
-YOU SEEN CATHY?

37:47.134 --> 37:48.831
-YEAH, SHE, UH...

37:49.354 --> 37:53.793
SHE WENT WITH SOME DETECTIVES.
SHE SAID SHE'D SEE YOU TOMORROW.
-OKAY.

37:55.055 --> 37:56.056
-AND, DAD.

37:57.449 --> 37:59.146
ABOUT CATHY.

38:01.235 --> 38:02.280
-WHAT?

38:03.324 --> 38:04.804
-NOTHING.

38:13.116 --> 38:14.683
-ISN'T THAT SOMETHING?

38:15.380 --> 38:18.470
THEY'RE GOING TO ETCH OUR NAMES
RIGHT THERE RIGHT AMONGST
THE GREAT ONES.

38:18.600 --> 38:20.689
-BEN, YOU DESERVE IT.
-SO DO BOTH OF YOU.

38:21.473 --> 38:23.388
AW, MITCH, COME ON,
SHE'LL SHOW UP.

38:23.518 --> 38:24.998
GO HAVE YOURSELF A GOOD TIME.

38:25.128 --> 38:26.391
YOU'RE GONNA MEET SOME ROYALTY.

38:27.087 --> 38:29.394
-I'M GOING TO CALL HOBIE
AND SEE IF HE'S HEARD FROM HER.

38:32.484 --> 38:35.182
-CONGRATULATIONS.
YOU RAN A GREAT RACE.

38:35.878 --> 38:38.794
-THANKS. SO DID YOU.

38:40.405 --> 38:43.364
-LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
PRESENTING PRINCE ALEXANDER

38:43.495 --> 38:45.888
AND PRINCESS
CATHERINE RANDENBERG.

38:46.019 --> 38:47.542
-COME. I'LL INTRODUCE YOU.

38:48.587 --> 38:50.197
-[SIGHS]

38:53.853 --> 38:57.335
-YOUR HIGHNESS, MAY I
INTRODUCE THIS YEAR'S CUP
WINNER, MITCH BUCHANNON.

38:58.510 --> 39:00.033
-VERY WELL DONE, YOUNG MAN.

39:00.163 --> 39:02.688
-THANK YOU, YOUR HIGHNESS.

39:03.384 --> 39:05.343
-AND THIS IS
THE PRINCESS CATHERINE.

39:16.092 --> 39:18.660
-CONGRATULATIONS ON
YOUR VICTORY, MR. BUCHANNON.

39:18.791 --> 39:20.749
I KNOW HOW MUCH IT MUST
HAVE MEANT TO YOU.

39:22.969 --> 39:25.232
-EXCUSE ME, I'M SORRY, I'M...

39:26.015 --> 39:27.930
NOT USED TO BEING THIS CLOSE
TO ROYALTY.

39:29.497 --> 39:31.499
-WE'RE NO DIFFERENT
THAN ANYONE ELSE.

39:32.370 --> 39:34.589
WELL, IF I'D MET YOU SOMEPLACE
ELSE, LIKE...

39:34.720 --> 39:36.112
ON THE BEACH PERHAPS,

39:37.723 --> 39:40.160
BUT HERE I CAN SEE YOU'RE
A PART OF A DIFFERENT WORLD.

39:44.120 --> 39:44.991
PLEASURE MEETING YOU.

39:45.600 --> 39:47.210
WILL YOU EXCUSE ME?

40:05.620 --> 40:08.971
-MITCH, I'M SORRY.
I SHOULD HAVE TOLD YOU.

40:09.885 --> 40:11.409
-LEWISTON?

40:13.498 --> 40:14.760
HE'S YOUR FIANCE?

40:16.152 --> 40:17.502
-YES.

40:22.550 --> 40:24.030
-YOU LYING TO HIM NOW?

40:25.814 --> 40:28.338
-I SHALL TELL HIM EVERYTHING
AFTER WE'RE MARRIED.

40:30.253 --> 40:32.430
-HOW CAN YOU MARRY SOMEONE
WHEN THERE'S NO LOVE?

40:33.169 --> 40:34.997
-BUT THERE "IS" LOVE...

40:35.128 --> 40:37.435
I LOVE MY PEOPLE,
I LOVE MY COUNTRY.

40:38.523 --> 40:40.394
JAMES WILL PROVIDE JOBS...

40:41.047 --> 40:43.441
INDUSTRY WHICH OUR ECONOMY
DESPERATELY NEEDS.

40:44.267 --> 40:45.530
-WHAT ABOUT OUR NEEDS?

40:47.053 --> 40:50.012
OR WAS EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED
BETWEEN US JUST A DIVERSION?

40:50.752 --> 40:52.624
-YOU KNOW IT WAS MORE
THAN THAT, MITCH.

40:54.103 --> 40:57.411
I NEVER KNEW WE WOULD
GROW SO CLOSE.

40:58.064 --> 40:59.413
-CLOSE?

41:00.414 --> 41:01.937
-FALL IN LOVE.

41:07.116 --> 41:08.161
-CATHY...

41:08.944 --> 41:10.990
-YOU RESCUED ME TWICE, MITCH.

41:11.120 --> 41:12.295
THIS TIME, YOU CAN'T.

41:13.471 --> 41:15.908
MY FATHER'S WAITING
TO ANNOUNCE MY BETROTHAL.

41:17.126 --> 41:18.563
I HAVE TO ACCEPT WHO I AM,

41:18.693 --> 41:20.347
ACCEPT MY RESPONSIBILITIES.

41:22.741 --> 41:24.525
WILL YOU KISS HOBIE
GOODBYE FOR ME?

41:26.571 --> 41:28.311
I'LL NEVER FORGET YOU.

41:29.704 --> 41:31.314
REMEMBER ME.

41:33.882 --> 41:35.536
-I WILL.

41:39.105 --> 41:41.020
I ALWAYS WILL.

41:57.689 --> 41:59.604
-MAN:
MAY I HAVE YOUR
ATTENTION, PLEASE?

41:59.734 --> 42:01.997
I HAVE A JOYOUS ANNOUNCEMENT
TO MAKE.

42:04.347 --> 42:07.786
-[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
